# GAB Protected Script (.g2p) Files

`.g2p` is the **encrypted distribution format** for GAB scripts. It is an alternative to `.g2u` + `.sig`, NOT a companion file.

## Format Comparison
| | `.g2u` + `.sig` | `.g2p` |
|---|---|---|
| Source code | Plaintext | Encrypted (AES) |
| Signature | External `.sig` file | Built-in `info::` hash |
| Editable in Cursor | Yes | **No** |
| Contains forms | No (forms in ScreenSU code) | Yes (bundles form designer XML) |

## Package Structure
```
file::<name>::<version>::<size>
file::<FormLayout1.xml>::<version>::<size>
info::<base64_integrity_hash>
data::<base64_encrypted_payload>
```
The encrypted payload contains the script code + bundled form designer XML layouts.

## NEVER Edit These Files
The content is encrypted. Editing will corrupt the integrity hash and render the file unusable. If you need to work on a `.g2p`:
1. Open it in the **GAB Code Editor** (decrypts in memory)
2. **Save As** `.g2u` to get an editable plaintext copy
